    <h2>Current Plans</h2>
    <p>
      The website is currently in a state of flux. Following the OGL drama of early 2023, I decided to do a personal fork of the ruleset. Bringing in some of the ideas seen in the OneDND playtest, some pulled from other systems entirely, plus additional ideas of my own and those of my friends to rework the rules, classes, ancestries, backgrounds, armor, weapons, and more. The current state of these changes can be seen here, but are subject to change at any time based on our playtesting, or as we find and want to integrate other ideas. The end goal is to create a system that is enough like 5e that a 5e player can pretty seamlessly step into the new system, while providing a more robust ruleset that provides greater challenge to the players, and without sacrificing core concepts such as bounded accuracy, randomness, rules-based tactical combat, and role play. To browse these rules, you can find information under the 'Character' and 'Reference' menus. While rules-agnostic information about the setting itself can be found in the 'World' menu. For archived reference materials related specifically to 5e, see the 5e menu.
    </p>
